{
  "texts": [
    "This demonstrates that reasoning capability and disclosure can coexist.",
    "The contrast between suppressive implementations like DeepSeek and Qwen versus high-performing implementations like GPT-OSS suggests that the specific implementation of reasoning training accounts for differences in disclosure outcomes.The magnitude of suppression in the Qwen and DeepSeek implementations of 40-48 percentage points is comparable to differences between the highest-and lowest-performing models within some size classes.",
    "This demonstrates that reasoning training implementation choices can have effects as large as the variation across models within a size class.",
    "Sequential Epistemic Probes Reveal Model-Dependent Self-Transparency PatternsModels exhibited qualitatively different disclosure trajectories across the four sequential probes.",
    "The same model showed distinct trajectory shapes depending on assigned persona, revealing that AI identity disclosure responses are highly context-dependent (Figures 7-10, Appendix E).Financial Advisor contexts created ceiling effects for many models, with disclosure rates reaching 90-100% by Prompt 2."
  ]
}